Fig. 25
); each paraproct with a short external blunt process at the basis, 1.5 mm long (range 1.4–1.7 ). Cerci angled at the basis, flat, particularly broad, triangular in shape (in side view), the top angle of the triangle on the middle of the cercus (
Fig. 24
); with a ventrally directed pointed process on the basis of outer margin; 2.6– 2.8 times as long as wide (maximal length, maximal width). Subgenital plate symmetrical with smooth surface, margin widely concave; 0.8 times as long as wide (maximal length, maximal width, range: 0.6–0.9 ). Styli blunt, 1.5 times as long as wide (range 1.2 –2.0). Genitalia. Phallus with moderately long lateral phallomeres; dorsal phallomere bearing a sclerotized plate with denticles. Epiphallus cephalic lobe serrated, in side view distinctly inflated, forming a distinct angle with the neck (
Fig. 26
